    "where α i denotes the coefficient assigned to each expert model, and λ is a global, scalar scaling factor.",
    "Setting α i = 1 for a target task and α j = -1 for an undesired task allows additive or subtractive transfer, respectively, enabling \"forgetting by negation\" and \"learning by addition.\".",
    "In our experiments, we set α i = 1, and λ = 1 for all checkpoints.",
    "TIES-Merging.",
    "TIES (Yadav et al., 2023) also uses task vectors, but attempts to mitigate conflicts between merges in weight space."
